# plan/facts/26-che-pass-1-unintuitive-but-correct-findings.bn
#
# CHE pass 1 (2026-05-03) executed per facts/25 strategy. 4-query
# methodical batch (S1-S9 sampling, 5-axis grade, U1-U4 unintuitive-
# but-correct filter, anti-echo-chamber check). Findings composed below.
#
# Key insight extracted: PRIOR cheapcode strategy WEIGHTED voter-pattern
# heavily; CHE pass 1 reveals that HARNESS is the empirically larger
