# ============================================================
# F1 — HARNESS-AS-BOTTLENECK practitioner-mutawatir L4
# ============================================================
#
# Concrete corroborated lift evidence (2026):
#   - LangChain: same model GPT-5.2-Codex, only harness changed →
#     Terminal Bench 52.8% → 66.5% (rank 30 → rank 5). +13.7pp from
#     pure harness work.
#   - Blitzy: 66.5% vs base GPT-5.4 57.7% = +8.8pp from harness.
#   - Vercel tool reduction: 15→2 tools improved accuracy 80%→100%,
#     -37% tokens, +3.5× speed.
#   - 65% of enterprise AI failures trace to harness defects (context
#     management specifically).
#   - OpenAI Codex team (Lopopolo): "execution environment, not the
#     model, was the early bottleneck."
#   - AI Engineer World's Fair April 2026: 3 independent speakers
#     named harness/context engineering as #1 priority.
#
# Grade: S=2 C=3 D=2 I=2 V=3 → 12/15 = L4 practitioner-mutawatir.
# U-filter: U1=1 (now mainstream, was contrarian 2023-24), U2=2,
# U3=2 (multiple specific predictions confirmed), U4=2 → U=7/8
# high-leverage composable.
lemma harness_is_load_bearing_lever_l4_practitioner_mutawatir_2026_che_pass_1
  proves True
  by audit langchain-blitzy-vercel-openai-aief-cobus-pappas-aggregation-2026-05-03

# IMPLICATION: in cheapcode's claim graph, the harness-quality axis was
