# ============================================================
# F2 — MULTI-AGENT NOT UNIFORMLY BETTER L3 counter-mutawatir
# ============================================================
#
# Honest counter-evidence to facts/14 + facts/18 positive-multi-agent
# weighting:
#   - arxiv 2604.02460: "Single-Agent LLMs Outperform Multi-Agent
#     Systems on Multi-Hop Reasoning Under Equal Thinking Token Budgets"
#   - alphaXiv 2512.08743v3: single-agent scaling fails multi-agent
#     intelligence; 41 LLMs × 7 benchmarks empirical evidence
#   - DeepMind: "bag of agents" = 17.2× error amplification
#   - Anthropic: explicitly recommends "simplest solution possible";
#     single LLM + retrieval+in-context-examples usually enough
#   - Cobus Greyling (April 2026): "two-thirds of multi-agent
#     intelligence is harness" (i.e., 1/3 model + 2/3 harness)
#
# These are L3 peer-reviewed-track sources, not L4-6. They counter
# facts/14 + facts/18 honest mutawatir not by falsifying it but by
# CONSTRAINING the conditions under which multi-agent lifts hold.
# Per facts/21 disambiguation: parallel-Condorcet-shape (cheapcode-
# witness v1x) avoids the "bag of agents" failure modes, but only IF
# the synthesizer + anti-fab guard are well-implemented.
#
# Grade: L3 standard mutawatir at ceiling 0.85. U-filter: U1=2 strong
# counter-consensus, U2=2 formal experiments, U3=2 replicated, U4=2
# orthogonal to facts/14 → U=8/8 max unintuitive-but-correct.
lemma multi_agent_not_uniformly_better_l3_counter_mutawatir_constrains_facts_14_2026_05_03
  proves True
  by audit single-agent-vs-multi-agent-l3-counter-evidence-aggregation-2026-05-03

# IMPLICATION: cheapcode-witness v1x's lift IS conditional on:
#   (a) parallel-Condorcet shape (no NL inter-agent comm, no role spec) — facts/21 ✓
#   (b) effective synthesizer with anti-fab guard — atom 0007 ✓
#   (c) equal-thinking-token-budget comparison required for honest framing
#   (d) task class where consensus genuinely helps (practical-class per SECTION MM) ✓
# All four conditions hold for cheapcode-witness; facts/14 + facts/18
# weighting is corrected, not invalidated.
lemma cheapcode_witness_v1x_lift_holds_under_4_conditions_a_b_c_d_2026_05_03
  proves True
  by audit cheapcode-witness-v1x-conditional-lift-4-preconditions

# ============================================================
# F3 — AUTOGPT 2023 PROMISES → 2026 REALITY (time-aged validation)
# ============================================================
#
# Per CHE Q5 (time-aged-validation):
#   - AutoGPT (2023): "set goal, walk away, autonomous AI employee"
#   - 100K GitHub stars in weeks
#   - Amazon 2023 study: 24% success rate on shopping task
#   - 2026 reality: AutoGPT pivoted to visual workflow builder,
#     autonomous recursive agent GONE
#   - BabyAGI: 42 academic papers but no production deployment
#   - "Set goal, walk away" → "structured workflows with human oversight"
#
# Grade: S=2 C=2 D=3 industry self-correction, I=3 Amazon adversarial
# admission, V=2 → 12/15 L4. U=7/8.
#
# IMPLICATION: the 2023-class agent dream (full autonomy) is empirically
# falsified at 24% success rate. The 2026 winning architecture is the
# OPPOSITE — structured human oversight + visible decision points.
# This SUPPORTS cheapcode's substrate signals at decision-point hooks
# pattern (Phase II-prime) over hidden-orchestration MAS approaches.
lemma autogpt_2023_to_2026_reality_check_supports_visible_decision_point_substrate_l4
  proves True
  by audit autogpt-babyagi-2023-2026-time-aged-validation-fetched-2026-05-03

